==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catch crop
<hw>Catch crop</hw>. <def>Any crop grown between the rows of another
crop or intermediate between two crops in ordinary rotation in point of
time.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Catch"-crop`ping</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms></p>

<p><q>Radishes . . . are often grown as a <qex>catch crop</qex> with
other vegetables.</q> <rj><qau>L. H. Bailey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catchdrain</ent>⟦br⟧
